NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, possess THC with intent to deliver.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 2.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) Maintain fulltime employment or schooling or combination or work search;
4) Spend thirty (30) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, to commence on 09-25-14 by 6:00 p.m.;
5) Spend an additional fifteen (15) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on 14 CF 52 only, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge.
Expungement is ordered under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of the sentence.  The Court finds that the defendant will benefit and society will not be harmed by expungment in this matter.
Defendant has credit for three (3) days.  (01-10-14 to 01-13-14)
